From David K Shute Subject Re Rumours about John Munsch writes In article rutgers viamar kmembry writes Read Issue of Wired It has a long article on the hype of I've noticed that every article talks with the designers and how great it is but never show any pictures of the output or at least pictures that one can understand Gamepro magazine published pictures a few months ago and Computer Chronicles a program that is syndicated to public tv stations around the nation spent several minutes on it when it was shown at It was very impressive what it can do in real John Munsch The April edition of MIX Magazine carries a story on which includes pictures of the unit a schematic of what's inside and some indication from the people at as to where they intend to go and in what MIX is a trade rag aimed at the professional sound engineering The schematic shows a central DMA Engine connecting and mediating between two Graphics Animation processors bit bus a bit RISC processor with math co processor Video Decomp module a control port an expansion port where hangs its double fast CD player DRAM an optional video port for editing video and on the outbound side VRAM to Video Processor to TV chain parallel with a DSP to sound They promise Red Book CD quality audio full fps video and a future connection path to your PC via a PC expansion I am not informed enough to have an opinion about the various means and methods discussed The article written by Philip De Lancie does cover the other machines mentioned in this I come from the PC TCP IP world and see a tremendous potential for bringing connectedness to the educated consumer seems to have the right business partners to make this Hope this David Shute EMAIL